3.title: Casey and Catrina's Rural Refurb vs. Gary's Girls' Quaint Cottage
3.plot: Catrina gets a bargain on a couple of houses from a house mover and plans to make one a main house and the other a guest house. She invites Gary's Girls to work with her and Casey to create a cohesive rustic design for both.

1.title: Old Houses Get New Addresses
1.plot: Flipping houses Texas-style means first you gotta move them.

2.title: Woman Cave vs. Home Office
2.plot: The Snow Sisters design a woman cave while the Slays create a home office.

3.title: Glam Cabin vs. Rooster Reno
3.plot: Flipping a quaint stone-clad house in Lake Worth, Texas.

4.title: Historic Telephone House Flip
4.plot: Flipping a historic Texas home that was once the headquarters for telephone operators.

5.title: The Bet: Container vs. Loft
5.plot: The Snows bet Randy that they can flip a house made from a shipping container faster than his renovated schoolhouse.

6.title: Hardwood House v. The Disaster
6.plot: Flipping a Texas home with heavy cosmetic damage.

7.title: Quaint Cottage vs. Tiny House
7.plot: The Snow sisters give a kitchen a 1950s redo in a little cottage that needs a lot of TLC; and Randy banks on his hip, movable house attracting interest at auction.

8.title: Custom Bling Closet Remodel
8.plot: The Slays see potential in a house with an odd layout and no usable closets; and the Snow sisters take a chance on a home that has been vacant for years.

9.title: The Slay's School Building Transformation vs. The Snow Sister's Reconditioned Quick Flip
9.plot: The Snow sisters expect to make a quick and easy profit on the vacant house they purchased at auction, while Cody and Suzi take on the challenge of turning a portable school building into a home-workshop combo.

1.title: The Young Guns' Over-the-Top Barn Meets the Lone Wolf's Live-and-Work Loft
1.plot: Cody drops a bid for a tiny backyard barn but getting it to the renovation lot takes a radical house move. Randy wins a weird square building with prison-size windows and he has ideas for an open-plan, loft-style remodel

2.title: Randy Gem's vs. Snows' Silo
2.plot: Randy finds a great house at an auction, but is hesitant to spend more money to update it, leaving Travis to convince him otherwise. Elsewhere, Toni grabs a small tin grain silo, much to Donna's chagrin.

3.title: A Country Melody Home
3.plot: The Snows buy a partially gutted home with an old piano that inspires a country melody theme

4.title: Dueling Duplexes
4.plot: The Snow sisters and the Slays score identical duplex homes and compete to see who can get more creative and make the most money on their flip.

5.title: Captain Cody vs. Randy's Shack
5.plot: Cody buys a houseboat and Suzi helps him revamp it into a party boat while Randy bids on a building that has no bedroom or bathroom and decides to transform it into a vacation cottage.

6.title: The Bird House
6.plot: The sisters remodel a duplex into a single-family home.

7.title: A Dollar Deal vs. A Retreat
7.plot: The Snows renovate one-room shack into a writer's retreat and the Young Guns tackle a horror house.

8.title: The Duplex Debacle
8.plot: The team battle rot and termite damage while redesigning a duplex.

9.title: Camo Lodge vs. Playhouse
9.plot: The guys win a 40 foot metal shipping container and transform it into a sporting lodge. Elsewhere: Donna and Toni build a playhouse to be auctioned off.

10.title: Divide and Conquer
10.plot: The Snows tackle a large house that must be cut in half to be moved.

11.title: Funky Flip vs. Quaint Cabin
11.plot: Randy updates a house stuck in the 1970s and the Snows renovate a pool house from a previous bid after getting outbid at another auction.

12.title: Snow's Rustic Western Themed Ranch House Renovation
12.plot: The Snow Sisters give a termite damaged three bedroom house a new kitchen and updated bathrooms and bedrooms with a rustic western design theme.

13.title: Randy's Vintage Airstream Dream vs. Young Gun's Rolling Retreat
13.plot: Randy tackles an Airstream travel trailer after getting a great bargain. Also: Cody rebuilds a shed into a small house after he has to knock a larger house because it could not be moved.

1.title: Shack Shake-Up vs. Old Church
1.plot: In the third season premiere, the Young Guns score a house that used to be a church, but cousin Casey takes over the flip when they go out of town. Also: Donna and Toni win a small service building and transform into a cottage retreat.

2.title: The Snow's Historic Renovation
2.plot: The sisters tackle their dad's childhood home.

3.title: Casey's Two from One House Split?
3.plot: Casey lands a neglected house that must be cut in two to be moved, but a Twister nearly destroys one of the halves.

4.title: Young Guns Garage Reboot vs. Randy's Modern Makeover
4.plot: The Lone Wolf wins a house that has major problems and the Young Guns grab a small service building and create a studio suite.

5.title: Ramshackle Restoration
5.plot: The sisters score a rough looking house that needs to be cut apart to be moved.

6.title: Guest Ranch Houses
6.plot: Identical houses are rebuilt by the Snows and the Lone Wolf and pitched to a buyer who's looking to add to a guest ranch.

7.title: It Takes Two
7.plot: The Lone Wolf bites off more than he can chew when he scores a large three-bedroom home and calls in fellow flipper Casey to lighten his load.

8.title: The Lone Wolf's Nightmare vs Casey's Too Tall Lake House
8.plot: Randy encounters water damage and black mold and Casey tackles a worn-down lakeside home.

9.title: The Lone Wolf's Nightmare vs. Casey's Too Tall Lake House
9.plot: Randy thinks he got a steal on a house with a stucco exterior, until he finds water damage and black mold inside. When Casey is left to turn around a shabby lakeside home by himself, he decides to hire a new hand.

10.title: The Snows vs. The Lone Wolf Rent House Rivalry
10.plot: The sisters buy a house next to one the Lone Wolf purchased.

11.title: Casey's Home Based Business Flip
11.plot: Casey discovers asbestos siding in a Fort Worth house and needs to cut off part of the roof in order to move.

12.title: The Lone Wolf's Empty Nest Syndrome
12.plot: The Lone Wolf tackles add ons and an attached garage to move a house.

13.title: Quirky Cabin vs. Office Flip
13.plot: The Lone Wolf grapples with a seemingly cute cabin while the Snows turn an office back into a home.

14.title: Container Homes
14.plot: Donna and Toni buy four containers to renovate into houses and hear from two perspective buyers.

1.title: Snows Hit the Rails
1.plot: The Snows score a vintage 80-foot-long passenger train car from a scrap yard, and they can't wait to save this piece of history by transforming it into a cozy home.

2.title: Flipping Two with Help
2.plot: After the Snow sisters get two houses from the same lot, they realize it may be a two-team job after assessing the scope of the work; to solve the problem, the sisters call their friends Jordan and Michelle Olgletree to help.

3.title: Curb Appeal Catastrophe
3.plot: Casey and Catrina win a home with lots of charm, but once they look inside, they find it has been completely gutted; across town, Randy wins a large two-bedroom house at auction and encounters a catastrophe of his own.

4.title: Bunkhouse vs. Flunkhouse
4.plot: Casey and Catrina's new find, a utility structure with a slab floor and no interior walls, is a big design challenge; Gary's daughters must find a mover for their newly-purchased home since Gary is unable to help them.

5.title: Industrial Train Car
5.plot: Gary's Girls buy an aging train car and plan on keeping its industrial look while adding some updates; Randy snags a relaxing ranch home but realizes it has a lot of termite damage and is too wide to get past the gated entrance.

6.title: Casey and Catrina's Woodsy Guest House
6.plot: Casey and Catrina score a house that is practically new. The problem is that someone previously bought it, tried to finish the interior and failed. Now they must fix the botched job to appeal to a buyer Casey has on the line.

7.title: Coastal Home vs. Cozy Ranch
7.plot: Randy is approached by a buyer who is looking for a vacation home with a coastal theme; Randy works to bring the beach to North Texas; Donna and Toni get more than they bargained for when they find an animal living in their ranch home.

8.title: Half a House vs. Family Home
8.plot: Casey and Catrina score a house but realize they must cut off half of it to move it and still find a way to make it profitable. The Snow Sisters get a large house with bonus rooms, allowing them to get creative with their design.

9.title: Tuscan Villa vs Modern Glam
9.plot: When two houses go up for auction on the same street, Donna and Toni snag one while their nieces, Gary's girls, win the second. Donna and Toni design a bright Tuscan villa while Gary's girls bring the glam to a drab two-bedroom.

10.title: The Container Collaboration
10.plot: Casey and Catrina combine two shipping containers to create a house with an outdoor courtyard area. During the build, Gary's Girls approach Casey with an offer to sell him a container house after their previous sale fell through.

11.title: Eco-Friendly House vs. Hot Mess
11.plot: Randy wins an old mobile home at auction and strikes up a deal with Casey so they can both make a profit. But before either mover can flip the house, disaster strikes. Meanwhile, the Snow Sisters come up with an ecofriendly design for their house. They hope that by making this house green, it'll put some green into their pockets.

12.title: Mediterranean House vs. Two Barns
12.plot: An arched entryway in the Girls' new home inspires them to create a Mediterranean theme; Casey and Catrina win two small barns in a two-for-one auction and plan to combine them into one large living space in order to maximize profit.

13.title: No Living Room Blues
13.plot: Facing a challenge of a large home with very big bedrooms, no defined living room, a small kitchen and dining area, Randy must redesign this ill planned structure with an appealing open floor plan to make this home a winner.

1.title: Randy's Hidden Shiplap Shack
1.plot: After winning a house at an auction, Randy quickly finds out that while his prize is riddled with issues that include a lack of bathrooms and termite damage, it also houses a hidden treasure within the walls.

2.title: The Snows' Modern Build vs. Casey and Catrina's Contemporary Crib
2.plot: The Snow sisters score a home with tons of potential and utilize the square footage to flip it into a modern masterpiece. Then, Casey and Catrina spruce up their build with a contemporary theme, bright colors and unique designs.

3.title: Gary's Girl's Big Bin vs. Randy's Disastrous Deadline
3.plot: Gary's Girls win big at a unique auction selling a 27-foot grain bin. Meanwhile, Randy scores an almost pristine-condition home but misses an important deadline, turning the flip into a flop.

4.title: Casey and Catrina's Total Knockdown vs. Randy's Lucky Seven Jackpot
4.plot: Casey and Catrina demolish a home to salvage their build while Randy tackles a ranch-style house.

5.title: Family Friendly Oasis vs. No-Go
5.plot: Casey and Catrina win a large home and plan to split the house into a playful kids' side and relaxing parents' wing. Then, Gary's Girls might have hopped too quickly into a new purchase and need to rethink their investment.

6.title: Beautiful Barndominium vs. Junkyard Jewel
6.plot: Casey and Catrina flip a barn into a 'Barndominium' while the Snows repurpose trash into treasure.

7.title: Wine Country Habitat
7.plot: Casey and Catrina win a house that was moved from Texas Hill Country and are inspired to create a vineyard-themed design plan that centers around being able to entertain family and guests alike.

8.title: Gary's Girl's Catalogue Kit House vs. Randy's Grand Colonial Creation
8.plot: Gary's Girls win a house that was originally built with mail-order parts and restore the home with an airy design plan. Then, Randy scores a home with 9-foot ceilings and picks up remodeling where the previous owners left off.

9.title: From Box to Bunkhouse
9.plot: Gary's Girls win a large, square home that needs a lot of curb appeal. They decide on a bunkhouse design and with the help of their father Gary, they create a home for an unexpected buyer.

10.title: Duplex Doozy
10.plot: Donna and Toni score a duplex at auction, but while one side is in great condition, the other side is a total disaster. Their design plan calls for combining the two sides into one floor plan to create a single-family home.

11.title: The Snow Sisters' Roach-Infested Home vs. Randy's Cabin in the Woods
11.plot: Donna and Toni win a home with a roach infestation and must clean out the house to make a stylish design free of bugs. Then, Randy must go to great lengths to move his cabin out of the woods.

12.title: Two-Story vs. Spanish Villa
12.plot: Casey and Catrina win big when they get a small farmhouse with a bonus room upstairs. They design a chalet-style home that makes the best use of the square footage, giving them their first two-story build.

13.title: The Zen Den
13.plot: Donna and Toni win a house with a bad layout and obnoxious paint colors. They realize this house needs to be toned down and create a design plan that is serene and relaxing.

1.title: Bare Bones vs. Moldy Mansion
1.plot: The Snow sisters turn a bare-bones house into a multi-colored wonderland and Randy converts a moldy home into an airy, rustic residence with a stunning kitchen.

2.title: Casey and Catrina's Upscale Upgrade
2.plot: Casey and Catrina reimagine a dated brick house by adding luxurious kitchen and bathroom features including unique tubs, showers and sinks.

3.title: The Snow's Custom Cottage vs. Gary's Girls' Tiled Townhouse
3.plot: The Snows take a bare-bones house and turn it into a customized airy home while Gary's Girls create a charming home using tile both inside and out.

4.title: Gary's Girls Craftsman House Update
4.plot: Gary's Girls preserve the character of a Craftsman-style house by mixing the old with the new and repurposing original materials.

5.title: The Snow's Custom Cottage vs. Casey and Catrina's Contemporary Flip
5.plot: The Snows renovate a fairly large house and focus on making the kitchen area custom and unique, while Casey and Catrina create a contemporary home with a true galley kitchen.

6.title: Paige and Raf's Modern Style vs. Casey and Catrina's Family Tree House
6.plot: Paige and Raf share a house they bought at an auction with Casey and Catrina, who put the house high up in the trees on their buyer's land. Paige and Raf combine their different styles to create one modern house.

7.title: The Snow Sisters' Industrial Surprise
7.plot: Donna and Toni are contacted by an old friend who is looking for a house to buy. Much to their surprise, the buyer requests a sleek industrial look. Even so, the sisters deliver a house that far exceeds his expectations.

8.title: Gary's Girls Elevator Barn Build
8.plot: Gary's Girls turn a bare-bones barn into a two-story house with special installation requests from the buyer, including a unique elevator.

9.title: Randy's Airy Atrium vs. The Snows' Raised Roof
9.plot: The Snows and Randy go to two auctions in one day. After Randy snags the first house, he and the Snows devise a plan to join together. They end up with two separate builds and literally split a house between them.

10.title: Randy's Bay Window Beauty vs. Casey and Catrina's Porch View
10.plot: Randy brings natural lighting to a big house while Casey and Catrina design a space that's perfect for entertaining.

11.title: Gary's Girls Latin American Abode
11.plot: After Gary's Girls win a house at auction, Paige is inspired by her daughter's homework and decides on a design with Cuban influence.

12.title: The Duplex Double
12.plot: Casey and Catrina buy a duplex at auction that Catrina plans on turning into a single family home. However, Casey surprises her with twin buyers that have different tastes in style and want to keep the home as a duplex.

13.title: Paige and Raf Go East
13.plot: Paige and Raf flip a house that gets a brand-new roof and a specific design style. Inspired by Raf's Boston roots, Paige designs a house with an East Coast aesthetic.

1.title: Super Salvage vs. Shiplap Pad
1.plot: Casey and Catrina salvage as much as they can to save money and preserve the character of their house, while Paige and Raf strike shiplap gold working on their kitchen.

2.title: Hot Lodge vs. Art Deco Digs
2.plot: Randy breathes new life into an old craftsman by adding a sauna in the bathroom and a galley kitchen, while Casey and Catrina put a Texas twist on their house's art deco style.

3.title: Money-Saving Design
3.plot: The Snow sisters want to keep their home's existing layout but it only has one gutted bathroom. To make the house more functional, they add a second bathroom and salvage what they can from the original house to offset the expense.

4.title: Knotty Pine vs. Chic Shack
4.plot: Inspired by its features, Gary's Girls use a charm-saving design to revive an old craftsman-style home. Then, the Snows get knee-deep in knotty pine and hope to reuse as much as possible while keeping their home's country charm.

5.title: Randy's Rec Room Reno vs. Gary's Girls Starter Home
5.plot: Randy converts an old garage into a gorgeous game room, while Gary's Girls create a family friendly home with space-saving elements.

6.title: Casey and Catrina's Door Debate
6.plot: Casey and Catrina don't see eye to eye on some of the design elements but eventually end up with a stunning family home complete with custom touches.

7.title: Snow Sister's Little House vs Gary and Jerry's Beach Build
7.plot: The Snow Sisters create a stunning space for a buyer who needs specific accommodations, while Gary and Jerry bring both Florida and Texas flair to their build.

8.title: Casey and Catrina's Kid-Friendly Home
8.plot:

9.title: Gary and Jerry's Portable Pad vs. Gary's Girls Upscale Upset
9.plot: Gary and Jerry convert a shed on a trailer into a traveler's paradise, while Gary's Girls spend more than they intended going upscale.

10.title: Paige and Raf 's Lakeside Cabin
10.plot: Paige and Raf win a small structure at auction and turn it into a lakeside cabin complete with an upper deck and other fun features for a specific buyer.

11.title: Randy's Big Bed and Breakfast
11.plot: Randy wins a huge house at auction and turns it into a bed and breakfast-style home at the request of a potential buyer. He plans different features and designs for each room to create a unique experience for each guest.

12.title: Paige and Raf's Fitness Farmhouse
12.plot: Paige and Raf design a house for friends with a passion for fitness. Their plan for the home includes a fitness room, two stunning bathrooms and colors picked out by "Random Raf."

13.title: Snow Sisters' School Bus Flip
13.plot: The Snow sisters land an old school bus from their dad. For the flip, they draw inspiration from his old travel bus and turn this one into a small yet functional travel wagon for a local aspiring musician.

1.title: Gary's Girls Fashionista Flourish
1.plot: Gary's Girls create a fashionista's paradise with a custom-made chandelier, a massive walk-in closet and other bright, stylish accents.

2.title: Winner, Winner, Steak Dinner
2.plot: When Gary gets two houses that came as a package deal, he offers one to his girls and the other to Casey and Catrina. Gary and Casey bet each other a steak dinner that their team will make a bigger profit.

3.title: Casey and Catrina's Kid-Friendly Home
3.plot: Casey and Catrina win a gutted house and turn it into a functional family home featuring a stunning kitchen with a walk-in pantry and decorative dormers on the outside.

4.title: Baker's Dream vs. Craftsman
4.plot: Gary creates a unique baker's kitchen featuring an original pantry along with shelving for pie cooling. Paige and Raf are excited by the Arts and Crafts movement.

5.title: Plush Palace
5.plot: Gary and Jerry design for the high-end look with a project that oozes elegance. Texture is king with a tufted dining nook and a single-piece glass backsplash.

6.title: Casey and Catrina's Refined Refuge
6.plot: Casey and Catrina give a home with a catastrophic interior a fresh, light look with an eat-in curved kitchen island and more.

7.title: Sideways Silo
7.plot: Paige and Raf turn an abandoned grain silo on its side for the basis of an indoor/outdoor living space.

8.title: Modern Vs. Creole Cottage
8.plot: Randy wins a four-bedroom duplex at auction and splits it with fellow flippers, Gary and Jerry. Gary and Jerry decide on a Creole-style cottage while Randy turns his half into a sleek, contemporary home.

9.title: Sun Santuary Vs. Mod-Rustic
9.plot: Gary's Girls brighten the interior of their cozy starter home by using wall-to-wall kitchen windows. Meanwhile, Casey and Catrina design a modern, rustic villa complete with an ornate, columned porch.

10.title: Classic Reno Vs. Messy Flop
10.plot: Randy takes over the renovation of a house that a client left on his lot. Casey and Catrina win a small house that is cluttered to the brim, and things get complicated when the original owner starts having second thoughts.

11.title: Gary's Girls Airplane Overhaul
11.plot: Gary's Girls visit an airplane junkyard and end up buying two old passenger jets. Positioning the plane bodies side-by-side, they use the space inside and also between the two fuselages to create a one-of-a-kind, high-flying home.

12.title: Ranch-Style Office Conversion
12.plot: Gary's Girls win a large home at auction that was previously used as an office space. They plan to convert it back into a family home, complete with unique features like a turret-style roof and bump-outs to add curb appeal.

13.title: Mod Escape vs. Music Lair
13.plot: Paige and Raf add a sleek partition and striped ceilings to make their small space feel larger, and Casey and Catrina include a secret music room in their modern layout.

1.title: Randy's Wood Ranch vs. Casey and Catrina's Chic Bungalow
1.plot: Randy finds a ranch-style home that's in pretty bad shape, and he uses a lot of wood materials to restore it. Meanwhile, Casey and Catrina design a quirky, chic bungalow with a young professional couple in mind.

2.title: Casey and Catrina's Southwestern Style vs. The Snow's Secret Room
2.plot: Casey and Catrina pull inspiration from southwestern style when they use stucco, arches and plenty of red and turquoise on their home. Meanwhile, the Snow sisters find a hidden room.

3.title: Paige and Raf's Super Suburban
3.plot: Paige and Raf win a house at auction, but only half of it will move. They plan to add enough square footage to turn it into a suburban family dream home, featuring a dine-in banquette, plenty of bookshelves and a study space.

4.title: Snow Sisters' Southern Colonial Home
4.plot: Donna purchases a two-story home while Toni is on vacation and brother Gary helps Donna get started. When Toni returns, she and Donna infuse a Southern Colonial style into the home with columns, trim and lots of molding.

5.title: Gary's Girls' Tiny Farmhouse vs. The Boys' Tiny Lodge
5.plot: Gary's Girls strip a lakeside house down and build two tiny houses with the help of their husbands. The ladies come up with an innovative build that has a modern farmhouse design while the guys create a tiny lodge.

6.title: Randy's Cedar Chateau vs. Snow Sister's Diamond in the Rough
6.plot: Randy completely changes the layout of his house and uses cedar throughout to create an elegant, rustic feel. Donna sees potential in a decrepit house, and Toni helps her turn it into a beautiful and spacious family home.

7.title: Cook's Kitchen vs. Atomic Ranch
7.plot: Casey and Catrina create a large, spacious home with special features in the kitchen like a cutting board wall and double lazy Susans. The Hayhurst brothers go for a slightly different style that's perfect for family gatherings.

8.title: Randy's Upscale Country vs. Paige and Raf's Snag
8.plot: Casey and Catrina create a large, spacious home with special features in the kitchen like a cutting board wall and double lazy Susans. The Hayhurst brothers go for a slightly different style that's perfect for family gatherings.

9.title: Hill Country vs. Cozy Cottage
9.plot: When the Snows and Gary's Girls both have their eyes on a set of linked houses, no one wants to lose, so they decide to each take half.

10.title: Snow Sisters' Fine Design vs. Randy's Rough Cabin
10.plot: After moving a house, the Snow sisters realize they don't need a section of it and sell it to Randy. The sisters make room for an open kitchen and wine rack, while Randy creates a rustic getaway with modern conveniences.

11.title: Snow Sisters' Amercan Gothic Allure
11.plot: The Snow sisters step outside of the box and give their home a gothic theme with beautiful windows and woodwork after losing a major portion of the house during the move.

12.title: Gary's Girls' Mountain Lodge vs. Snow Sisters' Family Abode
12.plot: Gary's Girls transform a frumpy dump of a house into a mountain lodge fit the Rockies, while the Snow sisters roll up their sleeves to create a family-friendly home out of a trashed house.

13.title: Snow Sisters' Updated Ranch
13.plot: The Snow sisters update a tired ranch house for a private buyer by eliminating the architectural issues and creating a comfortable, spacious environment.

1.title: Snow Sisters' Cozy Cottage vs. Gary's Girls'Architecural Abode
1.plot: H.D. Snow calls on his family to renovate a couple of storage houses; Donna and Toni take one house while Gary's Girls take the other as the friendly family competition begins; both teams make plans to reuse some of the homes' existing contents.

2.title: Hayhurst Brothers' Midcentury vs. Casey and Catrina's French Guesthouse
2.plot: After moving a house in two parts, the Hayhurst Brothers decide to renovate the larger portion themselves, while Casey and Catrina tackle the smaller section as a guesthouse; problems arise when a storm blows Casey and Catrina's house down.

3.title: Gary's Girls' Seaside Set-Up vs. Randy's Sensible Studio
3.plot: Gary's Girls get some help from Randy Martin after finding a small building on the land where they've moved a recent auction win.

4.title: Paige and Raf's Dutch Dwelling vs. Casey and Catrina's Cape Cod
4.plot:
Know what this is about?
 Be the first one to add a plot.

5.title: Paige and Raf 's Residential Roost vs. Hayhurst Brothers' Vibrant Villa
5.plot: Paige and Raf score big at a rainy day auction and convince the Hayhurst brothers to bring one of their smaller houses to create a guesthouse on the back side of their property.

6.title: Paige and Raf 's Dutch Dwelling vs. Casey and Catrina's Cape Cod
6.plot: After winning a modest home at auction, Paige and Raf team up with Casey and Catrina who recently acquired a lake house; the two teams come up with a combination and style that any home buyer would love.

8.title: Casey and Catrina's Rustic Residence vs. Snow Sisters' Country Cottage
8.plot: Casey and Catrina buy a two-story home but have to remove the second story, so they partner with the Snow sisters to supply and renovate a smaller house to complete their parcel of land.

9.title: Paige and Raf's Fancy Farmhouse vs. Snow Sisters' Addition Nightmare
9.plot: Paige and Raf win a home that was once a local government office and plan to turn it into a large family home. The Snows win a good-sized home, but they find out that all of the add-ons are going to be a big problem.

10.title: Classic Home vs. Eclectic Suite
10.plot: Gary and Jerry win a large house at auction but must split the house in half in order to take it on the road. As they renovate the larger house, they enlist Gary's Girls to help renovate the smaller piece as a mother-in-law suite.

12.title: Snow Sisters' Rustic Ranch
12.plot: The Snow Sisters win a large brick home and Toni convinces Donna the finished product will be worth the high bid at auction. They accent the house with rustic ranch vibes and create a floor plan that will suit a large family.

13.title: Randy's Shotgun Shanty vs. Hayhurst Brothers' Garden District Digs
13.plot:
Know what this is about?

-1.title: Casey and Catrina's Pooch Paradise vs. Randy's Functional Farmhouse
-1.plot: Casey and Catrina need a back house to complete their lot and increase square footage, so they ask Randy to team up on the property with a little house he already has.

imdb.title: Texas Flip N' Move
plot: House flippers purchase run down, almost condemned frame houses that have been set for demolition to make way for larger homes. They move the houses to an auction lot where they renovate the houses and sell at auction.
